$interpreted: Sophie: Where on earth did Rune go? It's so late...
Ru-yi: Hey~~Rune~~where are you??
Sophie: Didn't this street used to be incredibly dirty...how'd it get so clean all of the sudden?
Hutchinson: Sophie! Hanbei found Rune. He's over there.
Hanbei: Put down the broom! No more sweeping!
Sophie: Rune, we've been looking for you for hours! You've been...
Hanbei: He's just been sweeping, sweeping, sweeping. No matter what I say he just won't listen! I'm about to explode!
Sophie: Sweeping...no, it couldn't be because...
Sophie: Rune, this is a big street. You don't need to sweep here!
Rune: Rune...understands...
Sophie: Rune, have you been sweeping here because I told you to clean up?
Rune: Rune obeys...Sophie's orders.
Ru-yi: What a boof~why are you sweeping the street?
Sophie: Ru-yi, don't make fun of Rune.
Sophie: Rune, I didn't give you an "order". You're not a slave anymore. You don't have to listen to anyone's orders.
Rune: Rune needs...orders.
Hanbei: This boy has got to fix that. Not to mention get a bit of common sense!
Sophie: Yeah, but I don't know how to teach him...
Hutchinson: Don't worry about it, Rune has only been free for a short time. There's no way he can change that fast. He'll get there.
Sophie: Hmm...that's true. I'm probably just too anxious.
Sophie: Rune, let's go home!
Rune: Okay...
Rich Child: Hey! Stop right there!
Commoner Boy: What're you doing! You've been following us since the morning.
Rich Child: Hmph! My father just imported a Striped Prickear Monkey from the Valley. It's worth enough to buy a hundred slaves. You're just jealous!
Rich Child: Today I'll let you play with him! But you have to listen to me!
Commoner Boy: You're so short! Who's gonna listen to you? Also, my mom said your dad's a bad guy.
Ordinary Boy: Yeah! I'm not going to a bad guy's house! Don't come any closer! We don't want to play with you!
Rich Child: Oh no! If the monkey gets away, dad's gonna be pissed!
Commoner Boy: Hahaha! You're friends with a monkey!
Rich Child: Hey! You can't leave.
Rich Child: Darn it...why does nobody want to play with me?
Rich Child: What are you doing here!? Are you mocking me!?
Rune: Rune...is...awaiting...orders...
Rich Child: What are you talking about?
Rich Child: You want someone to command you?
Rune: Rune obeys orders.
Rich Child: You'll follow any command? Well...
Rich Child: I order you to be my follower! You must obey me!
Rune: Rune obeys you.
Rich Child: Really? You're my follower, so you've got to listen to whatever I say!
Rune: Rune understands.
Rich Child: Good. I'm Deo. You're...Rune?
Rune: Master Deo.
Deo: You'll really follow my orders? Are you lying to me?
Rune: Rune does not...lie.
Deo: Well, did you see that monkey?
Deo: To prove you're not lying, you've must find that monkey and bring it back to me!
Deo: Wow! Those moves were so powerful! Teach me, teach me!
Rune: Rune is...powerful?
Deo: Yeah! Stronger than anyone I've ever seen.
Deo: Okay, I formally command you to be my follower.
Deo: I order you to teach me how to fight!
Rune: Teach you...to fight?
Deo: Like the way you caught that monkey!
Deo: There are too many people here. I'll take you to my secret hideout!
